(23, 1, 'Huawei P20 Pro', '\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The Huawei P20 Pro is\r\none of the best phones the brand has ever produced, and it\'s still troubling\r\nthe top of our charts. Even if you\'ve never heard of this brand before, the P20\r\nPro is a phone that deserves its place among the very best brands out there. Its\r\nRAM 6GB and Storage 128GB</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Screen:</span><span xss=removed> The 6.1-inch\r\ndisplay is only Full HD, but that does help with battery life. This is actually\r\nprobably one of the weakest parts of the phone, as it lacks the color\r\nreproduction of its rivals, but it does come with a screen protector\r\npre-fitted, which is a nice touch.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Battery life<b>:</b></span><span xss=removed> <span xss=removed>Battery<b> </b></span>4,000mAh .The\r\nHuawei P20 Pro will get you a day and half of light to moderate use - it goes\r\ndown after a full month\'s effort, filling it with apps, but even still we\'re\r\ngetting a good day\'s hard use, which is great.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Camera<b>:</b></span><span xss=removed> <span xss=removed>Camera<b> </b></span>40MP + 20MP + 8MP, <span xss=removed>Front camera </span>24MP</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>The camera is the standout feature on the Huawei P20 Pro,\r\noffering three lenses... and they\'re actually useful. The resolution is pin\r\nsharp thanks to brilliant image stabilization, the software photo optimization\r\nis excellent and having that 40MP sensor has been boosted well by Leica for\r\ngood low light performance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" xss=removed><span xss=removed>Mini verdict:</span><span xss=removed> The\r\nmain issue you have to overcome with the P20 Pro is the fact you might not be\r\nfamiliar 